draw(circumcircle(A,B,C));
draw(B--O);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
dot("$O$", O, NE);
label("$68^\circ$", A + (0.3,0.2));
label("$x$", B + (0.2,0.1));
label("$x$", A + (0.2,0.8));
[/asy]

Since $\angle A + \angle B + \angle C = 180^\circ$, $\angle B + \angle C = 180^\circ - \angle A = 112^\circ$.  Hence, $\angle OBC = \angle ABC - \angle OBA = (\angle B + \angle C) - (90^\circ - \angle ACB) = 112^\circ - (90^\circ - \frac{1}{2} (\angle B + \angle C)) = 112^\circ - (90^\circ - 56^\circ) = \boxed{78^\circ}$.

ground_truth:
Since $O$ is the center of the circle passing through $A$, $B$, and $C$, $\angle BOC = 2 \angle BAC = 2 \cdot 68^\circ = 136^\circ$.

