label("$C$", C, SE);
dot("$O$", O, N);
[/asy]

Since $BO = CO$ (both are equal to the circumradius of triangle $ABC$), triangle $BOC$ is isosceles.  Hence, $\angle OBC = (180^\circ - \angle BOC)/2 = (180^\circ - 136^\circ)/2 = \boxed{22^\circ}$.

